ygData.messageBody:
Hi guys,

Well I joined the list on Sunday night and then came to visit Rodcet
on Monday and joined "Mystic Alliance". I dare say I won't get to see
many of you guys until the weekends due to the time differences. I've
also just had time to look through some recent posts and thought I
better fill out the Intro like a good boy as I didn't give much away
b4 =).

First name: Swin

Oh boy, explanation... short for Suwinfi which is made up from Sun,
Wind and Fire. I was given this as my middle name by my dearest
mother but been called it all my life. I think she maybe had been
smoking dope when she made the decision but it's grown on me. =) Plus
I'm a homo and I just have to be different!

Location: Peterborough, UK (Born and bread Englishman, although
father in the US Air Force and was stationed over here)

Gender: Male

Age: 19

Homepage: Umm.. I'm lucky I can turn my PC on let alone learn HTML =)

Status: Single, for the time being...although changes regularly

Main character: Well I guess my main char will be Eizen now, level 7
Cleric on Rodcet, also have my play rogue on there "Rubian"

Other chars:
Utini - Lvl 35 Erudite Enchantress - Tribunal Server
Dalmin - Lvl 14 Dark Elf Shadowknight - Tribunal Server
Lynta - Lvl 35 Dark Elf Mage - Luclin Server
Yizenthia - Lvl 20 Erudite Cleric - Luclin Server
Banbi - Lvl 16 Half Elf Rogue - Luclin Server
Tyna - Lvl 14 Wood Elf Druid - Terris Thule
yada yada... I'll stop there =)

Most hated EQ monster: The tree hugging "Holly Windstalker" -
Although I got my revenge with Lynta...

Fav. EQ monster: Brownies just 'cause they're cute!

Fav TV show: Sabrina the teenage witch (The only TV I can watch
without wanting to play EQ instead... well almost...)

Non EQ Hobbies: Eating out, clubbing, dancing (mostly after getting
far to drunk.. Yes, we can drink at 18 here), sun, sea, sand and sex!
Occasionally the gym (something had to give a bit for EQ!)

I work for "Thomas Cook" which is one of the multiple travel
companies in the UK as a financial analyst, so inbetween that and
studying for my accountancy exams, plus the above I don't have time
for a boyfriend =) (is that good or bad?) heh

Anyhow, I'll shut up now and go to bed.. night all and see you in EQ!

(PS: I installed Roger Wilco, took quite a bit of configuring for my
limited technical PC skills, added to the fact that the web site says
it's unlikely it will even work with my soundcard I managed to get it
up and running after over an hour, lol, so maybe you'll hear me too!)
